.TH "bee-list" "1" "2012-08-31" "bee @BEE_VERSION@" "bee - bau et einfach"

.SH "NAME"
bee\-list \- List bee packages

.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.SY "bee list"
.OP options
.I <pattern>
.YS

.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.P
.B bee-list
is used to display all bee packages that are installed, available, uninstalled or updatable.

.SH "OPTIONS"
.TP
.B \-a, \-\-available
List all bee packages available for installation matching
.IR <pattern> .
.TP
.B \-\-exact, \-\-by\-pkgfullname
Use this option, if you want
.I <pattern>
to match the full package name.
.TP
.B \-i, \-\-installed
List all installed bee packages matching
.IR <pattern> .
.br
This is the default.
.TP
.B \-u, \-\-updateable
List all packages that can be updated.
.TP
.B \-U, \-\-uninstalled
List all uninstalled packages.
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Print a little help screen.

.SH "ENVIRONMENT"
.TP
.B BEE_METADIR
Directory searched for installed bee packages
.TP
.B BEE_PKGDIR
Directory searched for available bee packages

